<user>108008476949811854609<//user><Name>Kevin Colaco< /Name><Time>1602194472132<//Time><Rating>3</Rating>< Text>
The mushroom risotto was amazing, the ribeye was underwhelming and the iles flottantes deserts was out of this world.

Two disappointments was we sat inside and clearly the service team was not used to having guests indoors as they were very loud in the way they communicated with each other....and the biggest surprise was when the server took my wine ($700 retail) and decanted it out of sight...I've  never seen that happen before.

I hate to leave a 3 star as I really love what they do here, and while it's normally my happy place my last two experiences (yesterday and 4 days ago) left me a little disappointed.</Text>

Wow! I can't say enough about this place. I went here on a Wednesday (Tuesday & Wednesday 50% off bottles of wine) and asked the waitress for suggestions on wine based on our food. She was SPOT ON. Ever wanted to experience France or love French food? Please go out and patronize this business! Every dollar is worth it.< /review>

< review>
We started with Pomme Frites as an appetizer.  Then, I had Creme of Mushroom Soup, split a Seasonal Green Salad, Cassoulet for my entree and finished with Lemon Meringue Tart. Soup was 4/5; salad 3/5; bean casserole 3/5; tart 5/5.  The Cassoulet  was a bit too thick. I like mine to be wetter.  My understanding of Cassoulet is that it is a bean casserole with duck, Andoule Sausage and a chunk of pork (salted or smoked).

For me, the best parts of the meal were the Pomme  Frites and the Lemon Meringue Tart. I find it kind strange that the best parts of a meal where the beginning and the end.< /review>

<time>1497450928769< /time><Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
Replacement for Le Chevalier - inherits the true French cuisine. Frogs legs, Snails are available, but also a simpler menu cooked with √©lan and flair.
Steak frites, etc.

This place still has the patio forth long summer evenings. The cost makes it a special treat, but it has desserts like Ille Flotante - so that all is forgiven. The wait staff (mostly) can speak French.

Great for an unusual romantic dinner or a proposal!</Review>

Yay something other than Redboy Pizza. I don't really care for Redboy pizza, except that they deliver, but Fist of Flour taste so much better. They don't deliver, but they just recently opened. <Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Mike does his best to keep this track safe and fun to ride. Sometimes the wind makes it hard for beginning riders - and be sure to have bug spray! Cover yourself before you even get out of the truck because the bugs are crazy, but only sometimes, apparently they can't fly in the wind and they don't like weather that's too hot or cold. The hamburgers are surprisingly good. Overall a great place.<//review>

< username>
Jamison Medcalf</username>
<Date>1555989509894</Date>< rate>
4</rate>
< review>
This location is a very good burger place that has an understated appearance. Small, simple, and with minimal decor but with better food than its looks would suggest. With plain brown commercial paper towel rolls for napkins and concrete floors the only real downside of this location is how it presents itself. The burgers and onion rings at this place are very good and they offer a small number of beers on tap. The price is reasonable when one considers the quality and proportions on offer. Given how easy it is to overlook I would consider this location something of a hidden gem, although the local students probably know it well. Anyone looking for burgers in the area should consider giving it a try.</review>

<Review>Food and wait server were fantastic but it was all the other non food things that turns me off of this place.

1. They share a wall with a nail saloon, the smell was over powering inside the bistro and had to move outside. They only had 2 table with 3 chairs at each.

2. To many tables inside leaves no room to walk around comfortably. There weren't too many people inside but if it was busy, forget about it.

3. Drinks served in a 'to-go' cup with wait service and the server had take your cup for refills since the drinks were behind the counter.

4. Wasteful quantity of food; there were 2 of us and ordered the only size basket of fries. It was 3 lbs of fries! we couldn't even finish 1/2 of it; waste of money and food! I don't know about their other items but it is served a la carte so you if you want a side with your sandwich you have no choice in what size you get.

You won't be disappointed with the hamburgers as they were delicious.< /Review><UserId.>112697252323988992749< /UserId.><Resp>None< /Resp></record></dataset><record>

<UserId.>115737070004350133412</UserId.><user_name>Bill Her</user_name>< time>

< Rating>

< Review>
In the world of burger mathematics lies the formula to the recipe of a place where the burger=B is to the power of 3, or scientifically speaking B cubed, or B^3, lets not forget mathematically explained 1(BxBxB) =(hence) Bulldog Burger Bistro. This my lady's and gentlemen is the burgers of all burger places. Yes, crowded into the Bulldog Plaza shopping mall hides the holly cow cannoli, the grand finally of the finales. This is no ordinary place though, fight your way through the tight parking space and this is where you'd find The King of Burger King, it's where he hangs out when he's not shooting for BK commercials. Every now and then Ronald from McDonald's comes in to get a real burger when he's "really" hungry after eating his .25 lbs burger, and In and Out came in and out of this place before they became "In and Out," it truly is like Carl before giving birth to Carl Junior. This my friends is where Rally's checkered out and brought burgers into Eureka! Now visually speaking they aren't there yet, they're right where those above where before they became how they've become, before visual appeals were more important than the food that's become the dodo of the poopoo. Please don't let the visual appeal fool you though, the place is currently going through some renovations, with that set aside, this is how good the burgers are at this place. It is awesomely amazing!, they definitely crossed their t(s) and dotted their i(s) when it came to the food. So if you want to stimulate and highly intensify your frontal operculum and the anterior insula(this is part of your brain people), then I challenge you to come to this place where you'll find each characters above dancing together in harmony to something they can all enjoy. You too can dance in harmony and sing Kumbaya so what are you waiting for? Go-on, C'mon now... Carry on...</Review>

<user_id>100463684944458184870</user_id><name>Kem EM<//name><date>1614186073781<//date><rating>5< /rating>< review>
I do not generally write reviews but I felt compelled to write this review after my recent visit to American Freight. I came across this store online while looking for clothing racks for my clothing business.. I dealt with the manager Eric who was so helpful and friendly. Although I was only looking for clothing racks,, I ended up looking around the entire store as the inventory they carry was just very impressive. They have a great selection of very good quality furniture pieces and appliances at some exceptional prices. I recently purchased a sofa set elsewhere and only wish I had visited American Freight first as I would have definitely purchased from them and wish I had. I am in the market for a new bedroom set and found one that I just loved. The quality and design seem superb and the pricing is much lower than similar sets I have looked at elsewhere. Eric and the other staff were all extremely helpful and attentive and took the time to answer all of my many questions. This place is awesome and I highly recommend that you check it out. Customer service is excellent and they really do have some very nice furniture and appliances at some really good prices. Highly recommend.</review>

< Text>
edit: on 5/31/20 I received a voicemail from eric offering a partial refund (10% + delivery fee) in exchange for editing this negative review.

we agreed for them to mail the check. a month later I haven't received any check. I've called 4 times and provided messages at the store every weekend since, no response as of 6/30/20.

original review:
________________________________________________
pretty bad customer service, good prices. tips:

1) be prepared to bug folks in the store if you need anything. don't call them or assume there will be follow up outside of the store.
2) don't purchase the warranty, it's useless + they will push you into using the manufacturer's one anyways.
3) call to confirm the day of delivery, since the confirmation calls don't actually happen.
4) keep $15 in cash for haul aways, the store may tell you it's covered but it is not.

5/11: ordered fridge. they promised a confirmation call, but didn't get one for the delivery date of 5/15. had to proactively bug the store to confirm that I should stay home the day of.

5/15: delivery folks made me cough $15 for the haul away, despite documentation that stated it was covered. also bent the frame of the fridge while delivering. also tried to re-use my water line despite having paid for a new one. after splashing water everywhere, they left when I pointed out that the water dispenser wasn't actually working since a water filter was not included.

5/16: condenser fan sounds like it's hitting plastic, so it's obvious the fridge is a lemon. tried calling for help, but the woman who handles phone calls said they can't help unless I paid for their warranty upfront, despite the fact that I didn't get a chance to sign off on the unit.

5/17: went into the store for help + to show them a video of the fan. eric told me he applied a warranty to the unit and that a tech would reach out to help. great service in the store.

5/17-5/21: tried to get follow up regarding the technician, even got an email from david saying that it would happen. after calling 20+ times and failing to get in touch with anyone, I didn't get any help.

5/21: tried to schedule directly online using the sears warranty eric said he gave me - but it wasn't actually applied. the online agent told me to go to the manufacturer, which I was able to make an appointment for.

5/27: the manufacturer technician fixed fan issue + water line in 20 minutes. still no follow through from the folks in the store.<//Text>

I don't shop too much any more (76 years, old) however, I still have my Sears card and needed to get
some sheets. Yesterday, afternoon, I drove over from Alameda to the Hayward Store on Winton. I used to work for Sears back in 1984. I worked in Customer Service and really loved my job. When I first arrived in America from Ireland, the very first Department Store, I entered, was a Sears Store. It was
on Army St, in San Francisco. Therefore, I have a strong attachment to Sears. I will continue now, with my review. It was about 6pm when I entered the store in Hayward, yesterday. The first thing that struck me was, how dark the store, seemed. To my surprise, I saw some Christmas and they were all lit up- the
light from the trees in my opinion, made the store look even darker. The store has an air of defeat and
lack of care. I hate saying this but, that's my impression. Now on the plus side, I found the sheet (had only needed one sheet for sewing project) that I wanted but, again the shelfs looked empty and sad.
Now, a change of pace. Soon after I entered the Bedding Department, one of the employee's approached me and was so helpful and nice. Her name is Claudia and she is such a great addition to
the store. I also want to praise two more of your empoyees- Pardeep, was helping to break in a new
employee whose name is Lavada. Pardeep, is just terrific. She clearly cares about the company she works for and all the customers. Lavada, has this welcoming smile and friendly attitude. She will be
so good as an employee of Sears. On that note, I will bring my review to an end. I enjoyed my trip
to Sears of Hayward and it was all due to Pardeep, Lavada and Claudia- I hope they get to see this.
Regards,
Rose Flanagan

< Review>
I have given this bakery two tries, arriving no later than 9:30 AM, only to find 2 trays of donuts in the case.  What donut shop has almost no donuts left early in the morning?  Half their cases are filled with drinks.  As to the quality of their donuts I'd say what I have tasted was good, but fairly greasy.  This bakery's lack of selection, a problem noted in other reviews, is a killer for me.  They have a competitor just down the street called "Donut Star" with similar prices,  lots of choices, and the best apple fritters I've encountered.</Review>

< Text>
Wonderful lunch combinations serving quality beef, shrimp, chicken or vegetables!
Meat portions are plentiful and apparently three ounces per selection.
The waitress brought three different sauces to dip your food in and you can upgrade your plain rice with garlic and onions.  It was very tasty.
Lots of side dishes available to add.< /Text>

This place has amazing happy hour food and drink specials. The table has the set up to cook as you go the finest meats. The rice is bomb too. They have a great lunch menu and happy hour all day every Monday. Every other day happy hour is from 11:30-6:00 i believe. They also have a course dinner menu  for anywhere from 1-2 or 1-6 people, all you can eat, small plates/appetizers, and a la carte.

Every time we've been here the entire staff has been nothing but pleasant. From the ladies up front at the desk to the waiters/waitresses and our servers. They are always polite, friendly, and check on us often, asking if we need anything, refills, is everything ok...etc.

<UserId.>116201178301074000688<//UserId.><name>Maria Luu</name><Date>1579382868597</Date><rate>5< /rate>< text>
We've been here at least 3 or 4 times in the past 4 months. They have a great lunch menu and happy hour all day every Monday. Every other day happy hour is from 11:30-6:00 i believe. They also have a course dinner menu  for anywhere from 1-2 or 1-6 people, all you can eat, small plates/appetizers, and a la carte.

Every time we've been here the entire staff has been nothing but pleasant. From the ladies up front at the desk to the waiters/waitresses and our servers. They are always polite, friendly, and check on us often, asking if we need anything, refills, is everything ok...etc.

The food is amazing. Not only is everything always served fresh, but it tastes so good!!! The meats, the sukiyaki bibimbap, the garlic noodles and their kaarage chicken...it's honestly food heaven!

I always try to go for something new every time we come here but the favorites always win and I end up sticking to those. For sure next time I'm here I want to some of their new stuff and the ramen!< /text>

Indoor capacity is at 25% max. Very strict on entering with only one person at a time to check in. Then you wait back outside until called. There were seating tables outside in their partial patio as well as inside. We had a booth inside and the table adjacent to our left and right as well as behind and front was blocked. <text>We always take the kids here (ages 3, 5, 7). It's expensive to do right but the happy hours are good and the entire event is fun. < userid>
101367190588268859351<//userid>
<Name>Kara Johnson<//Name><time>1546108379217<//time>< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
This is my go-to spot for holidays and special occasions. Love the atmosphere, food selection, and quality. If you go on a holiday be sure to make a reservation well in advance!

Food - Awesome selection and great quality, particularly if you splurge for the high tier items.

Price - If you do the all-you-can eat it's a bit pricey depending on the tier, somewhere between $25-40 a person. The weekday lunch combo is a great value (<$15 for a good amount of food).

Atmosphere and Service - I've been several times and have always had excellent service. The music is always awesome, and the booths are set up such that you can have a nice conversation no matter how busy it is.

Parking - The lot is shared with several other restaurants and stores. Be wary on weekends and after 5pm when the nearby Trader Joe's dominates a lot of the parking lot. I purposely go at opening (11am) to avoid parking issues.</Review>
< Pictures>
None<//Pictures>

<Text>This place is pretty much a staple in my diet lol!  Seriously though, the food here is excellent!  I probably come here every other week at least.  My fiance and I are simply in love with this place.  The quality of the meats and the delicious variety of side dishes they have here is just amazing.

IMHO the best way to go about eating here is to do all you can eat so you can 'play the field' and try everything and see what you like the best. We've got our ordering down and usually get the same thing every time.   We always order garlic fried chicken, gyoza, yuzu shishito peppers, chicken garlic noodles, harami miso skirt steak (the best meat on the menu!!!), and beef tongue :)</Text></record>

<Date>1533491064536<//Date>< Review>
Good food generally if you like meat but don't order the all you can eat.  For all you can eat, the time is limited for obvious reasons but they will delay your reorders to stretch the time and bring lesser quality cuts.  Even vegetable reorders were delayed.  Last night, never got the refill on vegetables.  It's classic  cheap buffet tactics and unwelcome when you are paying 300 bucks for three adults and two little kids to eat.  I personally would not go back being the person that pays the exorbitant bill.  Others in the family love the grilling at the table and it's undeniably fun to do, but worth it?  Mmmm. No. Do yourself a favor, go to a butcher and buy some nice cuts of beef and then BBQ at home with some zucchini.  Cheaper. Better.<//Review>

<username>Abraham Ramos< /username>< Review>
A great place to meet with friends. Tends to get busy on happy hour evenings, so make sure you get a reservation ahead of time to avoid having to wait too long. Even with the happy hour prices, the bill can run a little high so account for that if you have a large group and splitting the check. Meat is great and the cooking surface is cleaned and replaced when needed. Staff can be a bit inattentive due to the influx of people, but with a bit of patience, you and your group can have a great experience.</Review>

<Text>Having visited several of these restaurants across the country I was excited to try one close to my sisters. I found the menus to be extremely overwhelming. They would do better to streamline the choices. I also found several of the meats to be lacking in flavor. The Kobe Chuck meat was extremely tough. This was a huge disappointment since I have eaten this meat at several locations and found it to be excellent. I also found the pricing to be a bit ridiculous mainly because there were too many choices and it was hard to decipher which way to go on decision making. Going out to eat should be relaxing and fun. You got the fun part but it was not relaxing to deal with your menu. I highly suggest you take a closer look at it and see what you can do to improve it.< /Text>< pictures>

I am usually a believer that if i am paying to go out to eat i expect my food to be cooked when served to me, but this was fun. There is a cooking guide on your table to make sure everything is cooked properly. You even roast your own marshmallows for the smore dessert! <username>Jorge Garcia< /username><Time>1477945322378<//Time><rating>4</rating>< text>
We came on a Sunday during happy hour. Place wasn't the busiest but our server wasn't the quickest or most accurate. He forgot to bring our appetizer and got my beer order wrong.
We both ordered Ramen which was not as good as you would get from authentic Ramen joints but still tasty.
Their happy hour prices are great. For example they have stone ipa 60 oz pitchers for $12 and various appetizers for under $4.
We will definitely be coming back, but likely only during happy hour.
As a side note, there is no separate bar or TV's, so don't come here if you need to watch a game.</text>
